SIMPLE: mesocephalic
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mesocephalic
<hw>Mes`o*ce*phal"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Meso-</ets> + <ets>cephalic</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>Of or pertaining to, or in the region of, the middle
of the head; <as>as, the <ex>mesocephalic</ex> flexure</as>.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>Having the cranial cavity of medium capacity; neither
megacephalic nor microcephalic.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>Having the ratio
of the length to the breadth of the cranium a medium one;
mesaticephalic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mesocephalon</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
